By Ismaila Chafe  Abuja  – President Muhammadu Buhari has felicitated with journalist, lawyer, civil rights activist, politician and administrator, Abdul Shaibu Oroh, as he turns 60 Aug. 15, 2020. The president’s congratulatory message was conveyed in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Mr Femi Adesina, in Abuja on Friday. President Buhari rejoiced with the former member of the House of Representatives (2003-2007), his family and friends, joining them to thank God for good health, sound mind, and continued service to God and humanity. He enjoined the former Edo State commissioner to further deploy his multi-skills to touch lives and emancipate society, noting that such public spiritedness would never go unrewarded. The president urged Oroh to sustain his passion for the country, as “Nigeria is destined to take her place in the comity of nations’’. (NAN) Abuja - President Muhammadu Buhari has commiserated with the government and the people of Kogi on the death of Dr Abdul Atta, former Permanent Secretary in the Northern Region's Ministry of Health. The condolence is contained in a statement issued in Abuja on Monday by the President’s Special Adviser on… January 4, 2016 In "News" Benin - The Edo Government says it has received requests for loans of about N1.8 billion from operators of Small and Medium Scale Enterprises (SMEs). Mr Abdul Oroh, the State Commissioner for Commerce and Industry, disclosed this in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN)in Benin on Sunday. Oroh… February 7, 2016 In "Business" ABUJA (Sundiata Post) - President oMuhammadu Buhari, has expressed his condolences to the governor and people of Anambra State, over the gruesome incident that took place over the weekend, in which 60 people lost their lives when a petrol tanker crashed into a busy bus station in Onitsha. [pro_ad_display_adzone id="70560"]… June 1, 2015 In "News"